vulnerability.name: USN-6844-1
vulnerability.description: Rory McNamara discovered that when starting the cupsd server with a Listen configuration item, the cupsd process fails to validate if bind call passed. An attacker could possibly trick cupsd to perform an arbitrary chmod of the provided argument, providing world-writable access to the target.

statements.status_notes: CUPS could be made to arbitrary chmod paths with specially crafted configuration file.
